nts1.n: A SCENE IN BETWEEN W/ SAMUEL KNEE - AUSTRALIAN 80'S INDIE (R)
nts1.d: Sam Knee navigates and curates lost underground countercultural sounds with deep dives into specific sub-scenes, regions, years, labels of the near mythical 80’s post punk DIY indie guitar era and beyond, back to its 60s basement punk genesis.
Dedicated record collector and owner of Lima-based store Cosmic Soundz, Salvatore Dellepiane selects an hour of psychedelic cumbia obscurities, mostly vinyl 45s.

Based in Cotonou, Benin, which at the time was referred to as Dahomey, Albarika Records was founded by the French-born, Benin-based producer and entrepreneur, Emmanuel "Manu" Dibango, who had a significant influence on the local music scene. The label was instrumental in releasing records from some of the region's most prominent musicians during the golden age of African music.
Many of the artists signed to Albarika Records were known for blending indigenous African rhythms with Western jazz, funk, and soul influences. This made their sound distinctive and part of a broader movement across West Africa during the 60s and 70s, as music became a form of social and political expression.

nts1.n: IN FOCUS: EMAHOY TSEGE MARIAM GEBRU (R)
nts1.d:
An hour of spellbinding solo piano recordings from one of the most fascinating musicians of the past century. Born Yewubdar Guèbrou in Addis Ababa, Ethiopia, into an upper class family, she was classically trained in piano and violin, notably even performing for Emperor Haile Selassie. 
She was invited to study at the Royal College of Music in London, but her admission was blocked by the Ethiopian government. Dismayed by this news, she turned to religion, becoming an Orthodox nun, taking the title "Emahoy" and changing to the religious name Tsegué Mariam.
She spent the rest of her years living out these holy orders, first in Addis, and eventually in Jerusalem, where she continued to write and record music – a truly singular style of piano composition, as indebted to the proto-ambience of Erik Satie as it is to the Ethiopian tradition. 
This mix, selected by NTS, features recordings from "Church of Kidane Mehret", a new archival release from Mississippi Records, including previously unheard material.

nts1.n: MISSISSIPPI RECORDS: A SONG IS A NAKED PERSON (R)
nts1.d: Records, mostly scratchy 45s, received as gifts over the years, with standouts from Karen and Eric in Portland, Matt in New Orleans, and Khaleh Sousan’s Iranian 45 collection. Includes two unreleased tracks from forthcoming Mississippi Records releases, and Michael Hurley to set the mood.

nts2.n: THE MIND MATTERS W/ DJ Ldot Adot
nts2.d: This peaceful playlist is inspired by a music therapy writing course that I took at UCLA led by Esperanza Spalding. The music in my research that positively affected those that suffered from  anxiety were productions that had lower frequencies, low registers, binaural tones, and nature.

nts2.n: A Brief History of Peace On Earth w/ frecklequeen
nts2.d: Explore what peace has sounded like through recorded time. Music from my collection of rare New Age cassette tapes, film scores, and library records. Hidden gems for escape, concentration, relaxation, lovemaking, and astral projection.

Hulali is the Hawaiian word for sparkle, and Maluhia (my middle name) means peace. This is the soundtrack that I imagine plays as one ascends to the heavens; sunlight glimmering on the ocean, leaving the suffering of this world behind and resting in eternal peace.

nts2.n: Rest For Peace W/ Karl Gee
nts2.d: Raised in war-torn Lebanon, Karl Gee finds refuge in tranquil soundscapes amidst daily chaos. This mix drifts through ambient, spiritual, and experimental sounds for dreamy early-mornings / late-nights: not surrender, but a pacific fight for peace.

nts2.n: For the squirrel in my yard w/ Koni
nts2.d: A collection of Contemporary Classical and Ambient songs with focus on piano. Sonic blankets for grey autumn days, dim lights and inner calm. For doing nothing but gaze out the window while it rains.

nts2.n: A Slice of Peace W/ Aneliya Avtandilova
nts2.d: "I just want to be a little lighter than I am.” — Before Sunrise

I created a mix played for an utopic club that evoques an atmosphere of light, peace and fantasy where many genres confluence such as Ambient, DnB or Trance. I used vocals from deconstructed anthems, elements from nature and cords instruments colliding with strong bass to command power and beauty.

When I get anxious, I find peace in listening to music. Over the years, some songs have become safe places where I can take shelter and disappear for a moment.
Today, I’m sharing a selection of these dearest songs that have helped me so much. Hopefully, they’ll bring you a bit of light as well.

The divinity of the everyday has not been lost. It’s in constant holy flux — floating between birth and rebirth. The internal world is infinite. Here is where we can feed our inner flame, to eventually casually ascend and find peace within.
A serene journey through ethereal textures, soulful grooves, and cinematic moments, evoking calm, bliss, and quiet euphoria

nts2.n: OPEN, CLOSE LIDS W/ JOHN W.G
nts2.d:
A mix of sounds inspired by the still beginning, and ending of a day. 
Open and close eyelids toward a sky not quite light, yet already fading. Let the mind un-tangle and body loosen to tones, a balm to busy minds and tired eyes.

nts2.n: Affirmations of Peace w/ Ross Marmion
nts2.d: A relaxing, soulful and introspective journey through a variety of genres, designed to quell the emergent chaos of everyday life. Layered with gentle affirmations of positivity, possibility and renewal, inviting reflection, balance and quiet restoration.

This mix is a testament to loving friendships across continental distances and the way music can hold people together across that distance. We have curated countless playlists for each other over the years that has created a rich sonic space of togetherness. Here's to all the ways music can transcend borders to cultivate solidarity and peace.

subtle.d:
DJ & Producer, B-Say has been a Subtle resident DJ for over 3 years.

His radio shows tend to focus on the 140 bass music scene and aims to showcase unreleased/forthcoming music from upcoming artists, as well as premiering his own unreleased material. 

More recently B-Say has ventured out from solely DJ'ing Dubstep, with his bi-monthly 'Dub & Steppers Show' which he uses to premier his own productions.

Slick is a London-based Producer and DJ combining the sounds of Grime and Drill.
Expect sets to span from sparse wave and weightless to classic NY and UK Drill, with everything in between
J:KENZO is a producer and record label owner (Artikal Music & Lion Charge) from the UK. Known for his minimalistic dark tribal sound in the both the dubstep and drum and bass scenes since 2006.

DJ and radio producer TILDA will be live from the studio to kick off your weekend. She’ll cover all corners of electronic music as well as showcasing unmissable new tracks & chatting about motives for the weekend. 

Each month TILDA will be closing the show with a signature mix.

Live & Direct is the show that promises to make you dance and make you laugh, with your fave tunes that make you go 'Rahhh ain't hear this in time' and all the cheesy jokes from me, Hannah :) Lock in for the sickest guests and the most relatable stories about daily slips and hilarious situations I find myself in.

Following his widely acclaimed breakout moment winning the 2013 DMC World Online Championships, Jon1st quickly built an international reputation as a ‘DJ’s DJ’. Not only proving himself as one of the world’s most diverse and musical turntablists, Jon also established himself as an on the pulse club DJ mixing across the alternative bass music spectrum and as an in demand live performer around the world, as well as recording acclaimed guest mixes for everyone from DJ Mag to Boiler Room to Ninja Tune’s Solid Steel to Mary Anne Hobbs to Keep Hush.

Established in 2013, eatmybeat is a hybrid record label & club brand that was brought together by a group of friends with a passion for electronic music and building community. With diverse tastes, they support and champion the underground bass music scene through events and releases on the label. Refusing to be pigeonholed into a specific sound, they showcase everything from hip-hop, bass & breaks, through to techno, jungle, dubstep and grime. As long as it's tasty and full fat, you best believe eatmybeat are snacking on it.
Born in Sunderland, based in London, Kitschko's productions and selections display a deep appreciation of UK club culture, and an affinity for late night, introspective sounds.

As a drummer since childhood, Chacho has always had an insatiable appetite for new and unique beats.
Combining his love of global percussion, dark grooves and deeper low end frequencies, 
his sets feature a blend of dubstep, grime, garage, breaks, hip hop and other flavours from around the world.
